race.comment: ARMAGH (7) sets up well here off an encouraging debut at Ballarat over this trip, tracking the pace and working home well for a narrow fourth. He should be better for that experience and looks suited staying at 1000m with another soft draw. This looks a nice race for him. HEGELY (11) resumes. The debut run at Ballarat was good, finding the line from midfield for a narrow third. She's been tuned up at the jump outs and should take beating with natural improvement. TRUE SERENITY (12) is a filly by Extreme Choice in the Yulong colours for the Price & Kent Jnr yard. She's jumped out fairly well and should be respected. TABLE TWENTYEIGHT (3) was expected to do better first up at Tatura. Will at least strip fitter for the outing and expect more here second up with Blinkers first time.
